task.summary: Pycharm professional was used for this commit. Since it is more powerful and only costs 8.90 euros / month, Matthias Schulz started using PyCharm Professional for django development so everything is formatted correctly.
Fixed some of the warnings and erros that PyCharm was showing.
Fixed some more of the warnings and erros that PyCharm was showing.
Fixed some more of the warnings and erros that PyCharm was showing.
The html tables were made more beautiful through changes in the main.CSS file.

In the ingredients_data2.py file, the data for phosphorus was 1/1000 of what it should have been due to a unit error. The error has been corrected. There is no need for phosphorus supplementation. In fact, Matthias Schulz has reached the point where he is definitely getting enough of every single nutrient and mineral. The mealplan in question is called "Matthias Mealplan 3".
Some more instances of pprint were removed. There is commitment to move on from debugging with print statements to debugging with logging and using the PyCharm debugger.
Some errors. test_nutrient_profile_creation.py is not working. However, test_rawingredient2_creation.py is working again! Yes!
All tests are working again. Although: it is unclear why.
